---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Gaggenau Appliance Repair Los Angeles | 200 & 400 Series Specialists";
const description = "Expert Gaggenau appliance repair in Los Angeles. Certified technicians for 200 & 400 Series — Vario cooktops, steam ovens, wall ovens, wine cabinets & more. Same-day service, OEM parts, 90-day warranty. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Gaggenau Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-gaggenau-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "Gaggenau Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Gaggenau Vario Cooktop Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Gaggenau Wall Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Gaggenau Steam Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Gaggenau Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Gaggenau Wine Cabinet Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"Gaggenau Dishwasher Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does Gaggenau appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most Gaggenau repairs run $195–$680. Common fixes like a Vario module connection, door gasket, or temperature sensor are on the lower end. TFT display replacement or steam generator work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Gaggenau Vario modular cooktops?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — Gaggenau's Vario system is a specialty repair. The modular cooktop allows combining induction, gas, Teppan Yaki, wok module, and deep fryer elements in a single integrated surface. Failures include module connection faults (where a module loses communication with the control unit), individual module component failure, and the Vario frame electrical system. We service all Vario 200 and 400 series configurations."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you service Gaggenau 400 Series appliances with handle-free doors?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Gaggenau 400 Series ovens and dishwashers use a push-to-open door mechanism instead of handles — the actuator button and door spring system is a specific failure point we service regularly. When the button mechanism fails, the door won't open without forcing it, which risks damage to the door frame. We replace the actuator assembly with OEM Gaggenau parts."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Gaggenau related to Bosch?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — Gaggenau has been part of BSH Home Appliances (Bosch-Siemens Hausgeräte) since 1995. BSH is the world's second-largest appliance manufacturer. This means Gaggenau's core electronics and platform share lineage with Bosch appliances. Our deep Bosch repair experience applies directly to Gaggenau diagnostics and parts supply chains."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does LA hard water affect Gaggenau steam ovens?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Significantly. Los Angeles water runs 250–400 ppm — far above Gaggenau's recommended threshold. LA steam ovens scale the steam generator and water inlet faster than Gaggenau's standard descaling interval assumes. We set the descaling reminder to match actual LA water hardness, not the factory default, on every Gaggenau steam oven service call."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service older Gaggenau models?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Gaggenau appliances built over the last 20 years remain fully serviceable — parts are available through BSH supply channels for most models. Gaggenau's build quality means older appliances are worth repairing. We service 200 and 400 series across all generations, including the EB 333 and earlier wall ovens."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  /* Series cards */
  .series-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .series-card { background: #161616; padding: 24px 22px; }
  .series-name { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .series-sub { font-size: 11px; color: var(--red); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .series-desc { font-size: 13px; color: #888; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .series-features { list-style: none; }
  .series-features li { font-size: 12px; color: #666; padding: 4px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #222; }
  .series-features li::before { content: "· "; color: var(--red); }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-blue { border-color: #3a7bd5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-blue .tip-label { color: #3a7bd5; }
  .tip-heritage { border-color: #6b4c11; background: #fdf8f0; }
  .tip-heritage .tip-label { color: #6b4c11; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-vario { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-400 { background: #333; }
  .tag-la { background: #5a2a7a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .series-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- TOP BAR -->
<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Gaggenau Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        Gaggenau Repair.<br/>
        <span>Since 1683.</span><br/>
        Vario &amp; Beyond.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Gaggenau has been crafting professional kitchen equipment since 1683 — the oldest appliance manufacturer in the world. BSH Group means our Bosch expertise applies directly. The Vario modular cooktop means a technician who understands module-to-module communication, not just burners. Same day across all of LA.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Gaggenau Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRUST BAR -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Vario Modular System Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">200 &amp; 400 Series — All Generations</span>
    <span class="trust-item">BSH / Bosch Platform Knowledge</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 01 — ABOUT GAGGENAU -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Gaggenau</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The World's Oldest Kitchen Appliance Manufacturer</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Gaggenau was founded in 1683 in the Black Forest region of Germany — originally as an ironworks, later evolving into kitchen appliance manufacturing. It is the oldest kitchen appliance manufacturer in the world by a significant margin. The company has been part of BSH Home Appliances (Bosch-Siemens Hausgeräte) since 1995, which is the world's second-largest appliance manufacturer. In practical terms: Gaggenau's core electronics share lineage with Bosch appliances, our extensive Bosch repair experience applies directly to Gaggenau diagnostics, and BSH's supply chain means better parts availability than most purely luxury European brands.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Gaggenau organizes its appliances into two series. The 200 Series targets serious home cooks with professional-grade performance and clean design. The 400 Series pushes further — handle-free push-to-open doors, TFT touchscreen displays, the full Vario modular cooktop system, and materials that wouldn't look out of place in a Michelin-starred kitchen. Both series appear regularly in LA's most demanding kitchens, from Pacific Palisades renovations to Beverly Hills estates.
    </p>

    <div class="series-grid">
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-name">200 Series</div>
        <div class="series-sub">Professional Performance · Clean Design</div>
        <div class="series-desc">The entry point into Gaggenau's professional world. Understated design with serious performance — gas and induction cooktops, ovens with pyrolytic cleaning, steam ovens, dishwashers, refrigerators. All with Gaggenau's uncompromising build quality.</div>
        <ul class="series-features">
          <li>Gas, electric, and induction cooktops</li>
          <li>Wall ovens with pyrolytic self-cleaning</li>
          <li>Steam and combination steam ovens</li>
          <li>Wine cabinets with low-vibration motors</li>
          <li>Fully integrated dishwashers</li>
          <li>Vario 200 modular cooktop option</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-name">400 Series</div>
        <div class="series-sub">Architectural Statement · Chef-Level Technology</div>
        <div class="series-desc">Gaggenau's pinnacle product line. TFT touch displays, handle-free push-to-open doors, four-sided glass oven interior, built-in temperature probe, Vario 400 modular cooktop system. Every component selected for performance and visual integration into high-architecture kitchens.</div>
        <ul class="series-features">
          <li>TFT touchscreen displays — all ovens</li>
          <li>Handle-free push-to-open doors</li>
          <li>Four-sided glass oven interior</li>
          <li>Built-in temperature probe (standard)</li>
          <li>Vario 400 modular cooktop system</li>
          <li>Pyrolytic self-cleaning across all ovens</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-heritage" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🏔️ BSH Group — The Repair Advantage</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Gaggenau joined BSH (Bosch-Siemens Hausgeräte) in 1995. BSH is the world's second-largest appliance manufacturer — a group that includes Bosch, Siemens, Neff, and Gaggenau. The practical implication: Gaggenau appliances share BSH's electronics platform. Control board architecture, sensor families, and diagnostic protocols overlap with Bosch. Our deep Bosch repair experience — one of the highest-volume brands we service across LA — applies directly to Gaggenau service calls. Better parts prediction, faster diagnosis, more single-visit completions.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 — SERVICES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every Gaggenau Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All 200 and 400 Series models, same-day across Los Angeles County. BSH supply chain means OEM parts for current and legacy Gaggenau models.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔲</div>
        <div class="service-name">Vario Modular Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gaggenau's Vario system lets you build a custom cooking surface by combining modules in a shared frame — induction, gas, Teppan Yaki, wok module, deep fryer, griddle. The modular approach creates a unique failure mode: inter-module communication faults where a module loses connection to the control unit while appearing physically intact. We diagnose module-level vs frame-level failures before replacing components.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: module communication fault · induction zone dead · gas module ignition · Teppan Yaki temperature control · wok burner · frame electrical fault · individual module failure</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven Repair (200 &amp; 400 Series)</div>
        <div class="service-desc">All Gaggenau wall oven configurations including single, double, steam, and combination steam-convection. The 400 Series adds TFT display, built-in temperature probe, and handle-free door mechanisms — each a specific failure point. The pyrolytic self-cleaning system uses a door lock mechanism that occasionally fails mid-cycle, trapping the door closed. We service the full system including the lock actuator.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: TFT display failure (400 series) · temperature sensor · handle-free door actuator · pyrolytic lock failure · convection fan · heating element · door gasket · steam generator (combination models)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">☁️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Steam Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gaggenau steam and combination steam-convection ovens. LA hard water (250–400 ppm) scales the steam generator faster than Gaggenau's standard descaling interval assumes — we calibrate the descaling reminder to match actual local water hardness on every service call. Steam generator element failure and water inlet valve scaling are the most common issues we see in LA.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: steam not generating · scale buildup · water inlet valve · descaling error · combination oven mode failure · temperature sensor · door gasket · steam circuit blocked</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Refrigerator &amp; Wine Cabinet Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gaggenau 200 and 400 Series column refrigerators and wine cabinets. The wine cabinets use ultra-low-vibration motors to prevent disturbing sediment in bottles — when the motor begins generating vibration before complete failure, the sound is immediate and concerning. We test vibration levels, compressor efficiency, and temperature stability. Wine cabinets are fully serviceable with BSH-supply OEM components.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: temperature drift · vibration (wine cabinet) · not cooling · condenser coil service · door gasket · compressor · ice maker · control board · LED lighting failure</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Dishwasher Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gaggenau fully-integrated dishwashers — both 200 and 400 series. Gaggenau dishwashers share the BSH platform with Bosch and Siemens dishwashers, which means familiar failure patterns and excellent parts availability. The 400 Series push-open door mechanism adds a specific failure point we address regularly.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: E24 drain fault (identical to Bosch) · not cleaning · door mechanism (400 series) · circulation pump · control board · water inlet · heating element · spray arm scaling</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">💨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Vario Hood &amp; Ventilation Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gaggenau's Vario ventilation system integrates with the modular cooktop — a downdraft vent that slides out from between Vario modules, or an overhead island or wall hood that aligns precisely with the cooking surface. The sliding glass ventilation panel that integrates edge-to-edge with 400 Series induction cooktops is a particularly distinctive product requiring specific service knowledge.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: blower motor · sliding panel mechanism · speed selector · lighting · duct connection · grease filter restriction · frame alignment (sliding model)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-blue" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">💧 LA Hard Water + Gaggenau Steam Ovens</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Gaggenau's steam ovens are among the finest on the market — and LA hard water at 250–400 ppm is among the worst conditions for steam generator longevity. Scale accumulates in the steam circuit 30–50% faster than Gaggenau's standard descaling interval assumes. We set the descaling reminder to match your actual water hardness — not the factory default — on every Gaggenau steam oven service call. In Pasadena and the San Gabriel Valley (where water routinely reaches 380 ppm), we recommend quarterly descaling rather than the standard semi-annual.</div>
