<!-- 03 — TECHNOLOGY -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Gaggenau's Unique Systems — And How They Fail</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Gaggenau builds appliances that require specific knowledge — not just "luxury appliance experience." Here's what distinguishes Gaggenau service from generic high-end appliance repair.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Vario Modular System (400 &amp; 200)</strong> — The Vario allows combining up to six cooking modules — induction, gas, Teppan Yaki, wok, deep fryer, griddle — in a single integrated frame. Each module communicates with the control unit through the frame. A module communication fault (where a module stops responding but appears physically intact) requires diagnosing the frame electrical system, not just the module itself. Generic repair misses this completely.</li>
        <li><strong>400 Series Push-to-Open Door</strong> — The handle-free door on 400 Series ovens and dishwashers uses a spring-actuated push-open mechanism. The actuator button assembly is the primary failure point — it gradually loses spring tension before failing completely, causing the door to require harder pushing before it stops opening. OEM actuator replacement restores the original light-touch operation.</li>
        <li><strong>TFT Touch Display (400 Series)</strong> — Gaggenau 400 Series ovens use a professional-grade TFT display for control and recipe integration. Failure modes: display delamination from steam condensation (similar to JennAir Culinary Center), backlight failure while the touchscreen remains functional, and full display board failure. We test each component independently to confirm what needs replacing.</li>
        <li><strong>Built-In Temperature Probe</strong> — 400 Series ovens include a retractable temperature probe stored inside the oven chamber. The probe connector (the point where it docks in the oven wall) develops corrosion from the high-humidity oven environment. Connection failure shows as probe reading errors or failure to register. OEM connector replacement, same-day in most cases.</li>
        <li><strong>Pyrolytic Lock Mechanism</strong> — All Gaggenau ovens with pyrolytic cleaning engage a door lock during the high-temperature cycle. The lock actuator occasionally fails mid-cycle, leaving the door locked after cleaning completes. We service the actuator without damaging the door frame — a common botched repair when done without Gaggenau-specific knowledge.</li>
        <li><strong>Wine Cabinet Vibration System</strong> — Gaggenau wine cabinets use a specially-selected compressor with anti-vibration mounts to prevent disturbing bottle sediment. When the vibration isolation mounts degrade, the cabinet transmits compressor vibration to the bottles. We replace the mounts before the compressor itself fails — a preventive approach that extends cabinet life significantly.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🔧 BSH + Bosch: Our Knowledge Transfer</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Gaggenau dishwashers share BSH's dishwasher platform with Bosch and Siemens — the same control board families, the same E-code fault system (E24 drain fault, E09 heating fault), the same pump and motor designs. When we diagnose a Gaggenau dishwasher, we bring our extensive Bosch knowledge with us. Faster fault isolation, better first-visit parts prediction, and access to the BSH supply chain for common components.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0f0a15; border-color:#6b4c11; margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#c8960a">🏔️ 1683 — Why It Matters for Repair</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Gaggenau's heritage isn't just marketing — it reflects an engineering philosophy of extremely long service life. Gaggenau appliances are designed to last 20–30 years with proper maintenance. An owner who has a 15-year-old Gaggenau 400 Series oven with a TFT display failure has an appliance with another 10+ years of engineered life. Repair is almost always the right answer. We treat every Gaggenau service call with this perspective.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Gaggenau Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔲 Vario Module Not Responding</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Module communication fault — the module appears physically intact but loses communication with the Vario frame control unit. The control unit shows an error for that module position. We test the module connector, the frame bus connection, and the module itself separately. Often a connector issue, not a module replacement.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-vario">Vario System</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ 400 Series TFT Display Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Display delamination from cooking steam condensation behind the glass — identical mechanism to JennAir's Culinary Center. Specific zones become unresponsive while others work. Secondary failure: backlight failure while touch function remains. We test display vs. control board before recommending parts — replacing the wrong component wastes significant money.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-400">400 Series</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">☁️ Steam Oven Not Generating Steam</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Scale buildup in the steam generator — accelerated by LA hard water. The standard Gaggenau descaling interval is calibrated for European water (typically 150–200 ppm). LA at 300–400 ppm means scale accumulates 2–3× faster. We descale manually, replace the water inlet valve if seized, and reset the interval to match local hardness.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🚪 400 Series Door Won't Open</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Push-to-open actuator spring failure — gradual loss of spring tension until the door requires significant force, then stops opening entirely. The actuator assembly is a discrete component; we replace it without touching the door frame or hinge system. OEM Gaggenau actuator, same-day in most cases for current 400 Series models.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-400">400 Series</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍷 Wine Cabinet Vibration</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Anti-vibration mount degradation — the isolating mounts between the compressor and cabinet chassis lose their dampening properties over time, transmitting increasing vibration to the wine storage area. We test vibration amplitude before and after mount replacement to confirm resolution. Compressor replacement isn't needed in most cases — the mounts are the culprit.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔒 Pyrolytic Lock Stuck Closed</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Lock actuator failure mid-cycle, leaving the oven door locked after cleaning completes. The oven is safe and cooled but inaccessible. We service the actuator through the door frame access panel without disassembling the door — a controlled approach that avoids the hinge damage that improper repair causes. OEM actuator, typically same-day.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

