    <h2 class="section-title">Gaggenau Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How much does Gaggenau appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Most Gaggenau repairs run $145–$620. Vario connector service, door actuator, or temperature sensor replacement are on the lower end. TFT display, steam generator, or control board work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you repair Gaggenau Vario modular cooktops?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — and Vario is a specialty. The modular system's inter-module communication creates failure modes that don't exist on standard cooktops. A Vario module communication fault is often a connector issue, not a module failure — we diagnose the difference before recommending parts. Most Vario faults are resolved without full module replacement.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is Gaggenau related to Bosch?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — Gaggenau has been part of BSH Home Appliances (Bosch-Siemens Hausgeräte) since 1995. BSH is the world's second-largest appliance manufacturer. Gaggenau appliances share BSH's electronics platform with Bosch and Siemens. Our deep Bosch repair experience applies directly to Gaggenau diagnostics and parts sourcing.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can you service 400 Series appliances with handle-free doors?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — 400 Series push-to-open door actuator service is a regular service call for us. The actuator is accessed through the door frame panel without door disassembly. Pyrolytic lock stuck post-cycle is another 400 Series door issue we handle regularly — same access path, same controlled approach that avoids hinge damage.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How does LA hard water affect Gaggenau steam ovens?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Significantly. LA water at 250–400 ppm causes scale to accumulate 2–3× faster than Gaggenau's standard descaling interval assumes (calibrated for European water at ~150 ppm). We set the descaling reminder to match your actual local water hardness on every steam oven service call. In Pasadena and the San Gabriel Valley, we recommend quarterly descaling.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you service older Gaggenau models?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Gaggenau appliances up to 20 years old remain fully serviceable — parts available through BSH supply channels for most models. Gaggenau's engineering philosophy is exceptional longevity — a 15-year-old 400 Series oven with a TFT display fault has another 10+ years of engineered life remaining. Repair is almost always the right answer.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you repair Gaggenau wine cabinets?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Gaggenau wine cabinets require specific knowledge — anti-vibration mount testing, low-vibration compressor service, and temperature calibration for wine storage. The most common issue: anti-vibration mount degradation causing compressor vibration to transmit to the bottles. Mount replacement (not compressor replacement) resolves this in most cases.</div>
